27/03/2006
ATHENS, Greece -- Greece's new foreign minister, Dora Bakoyannis, met on Saturday (25 March) in New York with Matthew Nimetz, the UN special envoy for negotiations between Greece and Macedonia on the two countries' name dispute.
A Greek government spokesman said the meeting was aimed at getting Bakoyannis and Nimetz acquainted.
During her talks with the UN envoy, Bakoyannis called for a mutually acceptable solution.
(ANA, MPA - 25/03/06)
